wikipedia_page.main: Fred Molyneux (25 July 1944 – 1 October 2019) was an English professional footballer who played as a central defender in the Football League for Southport, Plymouth Argyle, Exeter City and Tranmere Rovers. He also spent two seasons with Wigan Athletic in the Northern Premier League, making 74 appearances.
